WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.610 --> 00:00:04.130
Let's do a couple of problems
where we estimate or predict

00:00:04.130 --> 00:00:07.390
answers to questions using
linear models.

00:00:10.270 --> 00:00:12.030
It sounds very fancy.

00:00:12.030 --> 00:00:16.550
But what a linear model is is
just using a line to describe

00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:19.000
some trend in data.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.490
With our linear models we
will do a little bit of

00:00:21.490 --> 00:00:27.390
interpolation and a little
bit of extrapolation.

00:00:27.390 --> 00:00:29.280
You might have already heard
these words before in your

00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:30.530
everyday life.

00:00:34.690 --> 00:00:38.830
Interpolation means trying to
estimate what happened between

00:00:38.830 --> 00:00:39.620
two data points.

00:00:39.620 --> 00:00:41.700
We're going to do a couple
of examples of

00:00:41.700 --> 00:00:42.890
that in this video.

00:00:42.890 --> 00:00:46.680
Extrapolation means we'll see
what the last few data points

00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:49.950
were, and see what that trend
would look like, and then keep

00:00:49.950 --> 00:00:53.720
on continuing that trend and see
what might happen if that

00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:54.950
trend were to continue.

00:00:54.950 --> 00:00:57.380
I'll show you some
examples of that.

00:00:57.380 --> 00:00:59.990
So let's do some example
questions here.

00:00:59.990 --> 00:01:02.050
So I have this chart here.

00:01:02.050 --> 00:01:04.650
Median age, remember median
is the middle.

00:01:04.650 --> 00:01:14.310
So if I have the numbers 3, 7,
and 9, the median is the 7.

00:01:14.310 --> 00:01:17.390
It's the middle age.

00:01:17.390 --> 00:01:21.900
So this is the median age of
males and females at first

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:23.750
marriage by year.

00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:26.650
So if we just look at this data
right here, if we look at

00:01:26.650 --> 00:01:31.200
1900, the average man was
getting married, not the

00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:32.730
average, the median male.

00:01:32.730 --> 00:01:36.080
So the middle man was getting
married at looks like at

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:40.930
around the age a little over
25, almost 26, while the

00:01:40.930 --> 00:01:47.030
median woman was getting married
looks at around 22 or

00:01:47.030 --> 00:01:48.790
23 years old.

00:01:48.790 --> 00:01:51.160
As we went through the century,
those ages got lower,

00:01:51.160 --> 00:01:53.830
and lower, and lower, until
we got to about 1960.

00:01:53.830 --> 00:01:55.410
This problem is interesting
irrespective

00:01:55.410 --> 00:01:57.010
of the actual problem.

00:01:57.010 --> 00:02:00.330
It's just interesting to see
this trend that at the

00:02:00.330 --> 00:02:03.970
beginning of the century, people
got married reasonably

00:02:03.970 --> 00:02:06.020
similar to when they're getting
married right now.

00:02:06.020 --> 00:02:07.950
But there was a minimum point.

00:02:07.950 --> 00:02:11.070
Around the 1960s, people got
married at a younger age.

00:02:11.070 --> 00:02:12.870
This was true for males
and females.

00:02:12.870 --> 00:02:17.420
You can also see back here the
age difference between the

00:02:17.420 --> 00:02:19.400
median male and the
median female.

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:22.370
That's just gotten smaller
and smaller over time.

00:02:22.370 --> 00:02:23.580
Now it's really small.

00:02:23.580 --> 00:02:24.910
So these are just
all interesting

00:02:24.910 --> 00:02:25.820
things from this chart.

00:02:25.820 --> 00:02:28.720
This is the actual data
from that chart.

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:30.160
So actually I didn't even have
to estimate it here.

00:02:30.160 --> 00:02:36.620
In 1900, the median age of
males getting married was

00:02:36.620 --> 00:02:41.570
25.9, that's that right there,
and the median age of women

00:02:41.570 --> 00:02:44.520
getting married was 21.9,
that's that over there.

00:02:44.520 --> 00:02:47.060
So this is just a scatter
plot of this data.

00:02:47.060 --> 00:02:50.220
We've just plotted each of these
points over here, these

00:02:50.220 --> 00:02:52.660
in blue, these in red.

00:02:52.660 --> 00:02:55.230
Let's do the questions.

